          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Often, the optimizer can eliminate bounds checks within an array",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "algorithm, but when that fails, invoking the same algorithm on the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "buffer pointer passed into your closure lets you trade safety for speed.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The following example shows how modifying the contents of the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "UnsafeMutableBufferPointer",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " argument to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "body",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " alters the contents of",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the array:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "var numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]",
            "numbers.withUnsafeMutableBufferPointer { buffer in",
            "    for i in stride(from: buffer.startIndex, to: buffer.endIndex - 1, by: 2) {",
            "        buffer.swapAt(i, i + 1)",
            "    }",
            "}",
            "print(numbers)",
            "// Prints \"[2, 1, 4, 3, 5]\""
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The pointer passed as an argument to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "body",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " is valid only during the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "execution of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "withUnsafeMutableBufferPointer(_:)",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". Do not store or",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "return the pointer for later use.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Do not rely on anything about the array that is the target of",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "this method during execution of the ",
